1
00:00:13,888 --> 00:00:16,016
We'd better just leave together.

2
00:00:16,099 --> 00:00:17,225
Where are you going?

3
00:00:17,308 --> 00:00:18,518
Why are you leaving?

4
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:19,811
Let's go to the library.

5
00:00:19,894 --> 00:00:21,229
- I've secured all the…
- No.

6
00:00:21,312 --> 00:00:23,606
<i>We're going to the basement.</i>
<i>It's safer there.</i>

7
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:29,612
What? Ando's dead?

8
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:31,406
<i>Yes, George. He was stabbed.</i>

9
00:00:31,489 --> 00:00:34,409
Even though Sir Amando denies it,
he killed Ando.

10
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:37,203
And now, he wants us all
to go to the library,

11
00:00:37,287 --> 00:00:38,621
so he can kill us there.

12
00:00:38,705 --> 00:00:40,540
He's going to pay. He's an animal.

13
00:00:40,623 --> 00:00:42,375
Dad, don't. I won't let you die.

14
00:00:42,459 --> 00:00:44,919
- Jericho, let's go downstairs.
- Let's go.

15
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:48,339
<i>Amando… Why do you have a knife?</i>

16
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:50,258
<i>I don't know about the murders here.</i>

17
00:00:50,341 --> 00:00:51,509
Get away from him.

18
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:52,427
Get away.

19
00:00:52,510 --> 00:00:57,015
PREVIOUSLY

20
00:00:57,098 --> 00:00:59,017
Sam, what's going on there?

21
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,935
Give me the baby.

22
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:05,231
My son. My son.

23
00:01:05,315 --> 00:01:07,025
Did Aurora take the baby?

24
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:08,651
Maybe Sam needs help.

25
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:11,279
<i>Go to the other house first.</i>
<i>Use this first.</i>

26
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:14,866
Don't forsake your Ma'am Aurora
and our grandson alone.

27
00:01:14,949 --> 00:01:16,159
And Samantha too.

28
00:01:16,242 --> 00:01:19,245
Make sure nothing bad happens
to her and Aunt Mercy.

29
00:01:19,329 --> 00:01:21,456
<i>You know what you're doing</i>
<i>is wrong, Auntie.</i>

30
00:01:21,539 --> 00:01:25,919
<i>So, please put down your gun</i>
<i>and give me Sam's baby.</i>

31
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:27,921
<i>How about you?</i>

32
00:01:28,004 --> 00:01:30,131
<i>Would you allow it if Sir Paco was taken</i>
<i>from you when he was still young?</i>

33
00:01:30,215 --> 00:01:32,801
<i>I shouldn't have taken him from Sam.</i>

34
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:34,677
<i>Here, take him.</i>

35
00:01:36,387 --> 00:01:37,806
<i>You fool.</i>

36
00:01:37,889 --> 00:01:42,143
<i>No one can take Paco's son away from me.</i>

37
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:43,853
Whoever you are, I'm not afraid of you.

38
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:56,616
You are the Palacios killer.

39
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:03,289
Where did the gunshots come from?

40
00:02:03,373 --> 00:02:06,668
Sam, what's going on over there?
We heard gunshots.

41
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:09,629
Oh, my God.
I told Sam to turn off the radio.

42
00:02:09,712 --> 00:02:10,755
Bill…

43
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:13,633
Maybe the gunshots we heard
came from his gun.

44
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:16,636
Oh, my God. No.

45
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,055
That's Bill.

46
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:21,182
The Palacios killer murdered Bill.

47
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:22,851
Amando killed him.

48
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:35,530
My son… Mother.

49
00:02:36,114 --> 00:02:38,491
Where is my son? Mother.

50
00:02:39,784 --> 00:02:40,618
Mother.

51
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:43,872
Mother. Mother.

52
00:02:44,455 --> 00:02:45,623
Mother.

53
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:47,375
What happened to you, Mother?

54
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:49,252
Mother. My God.

55
00:02:49,335 --> 00:02:53,214
Mother, what happened to you?
Where is my son? Where is Mom Aurora?

56
00:02:53,798 --> 00:02:56,217
Aurora… I saw her.

57
00:02:56,301 --> 00:02:58,011
She took the baby.

58
00:02:59,178 --> 00:03:00,388
Where did they go?

59
00:03:00,471 --> 00:03:02,932
I don't know.
I wasn't able to follow them.

60
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:05,310
Where are they?

61
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:10,523
You monster.

62
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,735
Aurora.

63
00:03:13,818 --> 00:03:15,111
You're an animal.

64
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:27,040
PO3 Cruz.

65
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:30,043
Sergeant Royales.

66
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,839
Thank you for meeting with me.

67
00:03:36,966 --> 00:03:39,385
Like I told you when I called you,

68
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:42,847
I'm in charge of the Palacios murder case.

69
00:03:45,016 --> 00:03:48,478
I dug through the Palacioses histories,

70
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:51,147
and your name came up when I came across

71
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:54,317
the case of Dr. Orlando Castillo.

72
00:03:57,987 --> 00:04:01,699
Five years ago,
Dr. Castillo was found dead.

73
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:04,577
You and your team were the ones
who found his body.

74
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:06,704
I just wanted to ask a few questions.

75
00:04:09,249 --> 00:04:10,541
Go ahead, Sarge.

76
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:14,045
Why does it seem like
the investigation was rushed?

77
00:04:20,593 --> 00:04:22,679
You didn't send

78
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:26,849
the drug paraphernalia found in
Dr. Castillo's apartment to the crime lab.

79
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:31,020
And then you immediately confirmed that
the cause of death was a drug overdose,

80
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,523
even without proper testing
from the forensic team.

81
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:36,025
And then you immediately closed the case.

82
00:04:38,069 --> 00:04:40,947
The initial medico-legal results said

83
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:44,575
that Doc Orly died of a heroin overdose.

84
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:45,743
What?

85
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:48,371
Did Dad do drugs?

86
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:50,456
No.

87
00:04:51,249 --> 00:04:54,919
My Dad is not an addict…
and he would never kill himself.

88
00:04:56,170 --> 00:05:00,383
Ma'am, we found a lot
of paraphernalia in his room.

89
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:15,898
Wait, sir. No. My Dad is a good person.
My Dad is a doctor.

90
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:19,068
Ma'am, we can't say for sure.

91
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:21,696
Sometimes, the decent ones

92
00:05:22,196 --> 00:05:24,991
are the ones who hide their stench.

93
00:05:25,074 --> 00:05:26,534
Wait, sir?

94
00:05:26,617 --> 00:05:29,454
Didn't you hear me?
My Dad is a good person.

95
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:30,997
Do your job.

96
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:32,498
Investigate.

97
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:35,835
I know something is going on there…
at the mines.

98
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:38,296
Investigate. Ask the people there.

99
00:05:38,379 --> 00:05:40,173
Do your job.

100
00:05:40,256 --> 00:05:41,799
Maybe there's foul play here.

101
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:44,135
Mom, no. What?
Are we just going to let this happen?

102
00:05:44,218 --> 00:05:46,596
Are we just going to accept
that Dad committed suicide?

103
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:48,181
We know he wouldn't do that.

104
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:50,683
Dad didn't commit suicide.

105
00:05:51,559 --> 00:05:52,935
PO3 Cruz,

106
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:57,774
I saw a lot of irregularities
in your investigation.

107
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:03,488
Because my superior interfered
in the case.

108
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:14,248
Dad…

109
00:06:18,878 --> 00:06:20,088
I'm sorry, Sofia.

110
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:22,507
I'm sorry, George.

111
00:06:23,424 --> 00:06:25,343
Why are you apologizing, Dad?

112
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:31,641
You all got involved
in the Palacios family's mess.

113
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:33,893
All of you.

114
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:36,646
Jericho, Sam…

115
00:06:36,729 --> 00:06:37,688
Everyone.

116
00:06:39,941 --> 00:06:43,027
This family has committed so many sins

117
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:46,114
against our business partners,

118
00:06:46,739 --> 00:06:48,366
against our employees,

119
00:06:48,449 --> 00:06:50,576
against the people around us.

120
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:52,995
And this is the price of it all.

121
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,915
We are being killed one by one.

122
00:06:56,707 --> 00:06:57,959
And what's painful is,

123
00:06:58,876 --> 00:07:00,419
that you too are being targeted.

124
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,798
Dad, you didn't want this.

125
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:06,134
No, George,

126
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:11,264
but I wish I had done something
to stop this.

127
00:07:12,723 --> 00:07:15,017
I should've stood my ground.

128
00:07:17,311 --> 00:07:18,938
Did you rig the case?

129
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:24,235
PO3 Cruz… we are law enforcement officers.

130
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:28,030
That's why our image is being ruined
because of people like you.

131
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:32,285
By those who are paid, bribed,
and who don't care.

132
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:35,455
Who is your superior?

133
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:39,667
And do you know
who ordered him to rig the case?

134
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:44,338
It's Sergeant Reynaldo.

135
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:47,842
I don't know who ordered him.

136
00:07:49,594 --> 00:07:51,804
I just followed his orders

137
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:56,392
to make it look like
Dr. Castillo died of suicide

138
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:59,020
through a heroin overdose.

139
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:00,980
Because he paid you?

140
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:07,320
Where is Sergeant Reynaldo?

141
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:13,784
He was killed by the syndicates
he extorted money from.

142
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:18,414
But, if you want

143
00:08:18,998 --> 00:08:20,750
to reopen the case…

144
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:26,130
Here are the answers to your questions.

145
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:31,802
Why are you doing this?

146
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,304
Why are you helping me?

147
00:08:35,431 --> 00:08:36,891
Because

148
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:40,645
I'm already being charged
for all my foolishness.

149
00:08:41,896 --> 00:08:45,441
I want to pay at least a little

150
00:08:46,442 --> 00:08:48,319
before I die.

151
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,038
I have…

152
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:07,255
I have prostate cancer.

153
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:09,632
Stage four.

154
00:09:10,841 --> 00:09:14,053
It has spread to my bones, lungs,

155
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,888
liver.

156
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:20,268
So, while I'm still alive,

157
00:09:21,978 --> 00:09:26,816
I want to at least correct my mistakes.

158
00:09:29,694 --> 00:09:33,030
Those files contain

159
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:37,368
all my true findings
from the investigation.

160
00:09:38,452 --> 00:09:42,623
Dr. Castillo's heroin overdose
was intentional.

161
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:45,001
He did not kill himself.

162
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,795
Who overdosed him?

163
00:09:58,556 --> 00:09:59,849
Amando Namas?

164
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,435
All the evil was rooted

165
00:10:03,519 --> 00:10:04,562
in Dad.

166
00:10:05,646 --> 00:10:07,773
He is cruel and greedy.

167
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:11,777
In his obsession to preserve
Palacios Mining,

168
00:10:12,653 --> 00:10:14,071
he became a monster.

169
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:17,158
And Aurora inherited that.

170
00:10:17,241 --> 00:10:21,329
First commandment of Golden Palacios,

171
00:10:21,829 --> 00:10:24,790
Thou shall not steal my gold.

172
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:28,210
Because the punishment is death.

173
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:34,342
Ma'am, have mercy.

174
00:10:34,425 --> 00:10:35,676
It won't happen again.

175
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,053
It really won't happen again.

176
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:38,220
Ma'am.

177
00:10:43,517 --> 00:10:45,186
Aren't you worried?

178
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:49,398
Royales might find out
what you did to the Beringuela couple.

179
00:10:50,024 --> 00:10:52,068
What I did?

180
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:53,235
We did it.

181
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:55,655
Aurora, I was against it,

182
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:57,239
but you just forced me.

183
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:58,949
Calm down.

184
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:01,702
Help. Help.

185
00:11:01,786 --> 00:11:03,537
Hello, Sam.

186
00:11:06,332 --> 00:11:07,833
Did I scare you?

187
00:11:09,126 --> 00:11:10,336
You?

188
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,546
Welcome to your new home.

189
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:15,216
You fool. Why did you lock me up here?

190
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:16,926
You're so evil. You're evil.

191
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:19,345
You're so evil.

192
00:11:33,734 --> 00:11:34,944
You're so evil.

193
00:11:44,203 --> 00:11:48,124
Dad, is that why your position
was bequeathed to Aunt Aurora?

194
00:11:52,169 --> 00:11:56,215
Not only did Dad bequeath
the company to Aurora,

195
00:11:57,049 --> 00:12:01,846
but his evil and greed
for money and power.

196
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:07,184
Instead of stopping
the evil in this family,

197
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:11,188
I supported Aurora in what she did.

198
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:13,816
Please stop blaming yourself.

199
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:17,445
But, I can't help it.

200
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:21,449
I also committed a huge sin.

201
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:26,454
I was also blinded.

202
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:28,247
I envied Aurora.

203
00:12:28,747 --> 00:12:30,624
I also wanted what she had.

204
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:33,919
Wealth and power.

205
00:12:35,546 --> 00:12:36,964
But, I was weak.

206
00:12:37,965 --> 00:12:39,717
I wasn't as brave as she was.

207
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:43,304
So, instead of stopping her,

208
00:12:44,054 --> 00:12:46,223
I became submissive to her.

209
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:50,561
I'm sorry.

210
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:52,813
I'm weak.

211
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:56,400
I'm so weak.

212
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:57,651
Dad, Dad…

213
00:13:19,006 --> 00:13:20,841
I promise you.

214
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:24,553
After this mess with Amando is over,

215
00:13:26,096 --> 00:13:27,431
I will do

216
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:31,143
what is right
even if I have to fight Aurora.

217
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:33,938
And this time,

218
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:37,066
I will be stronger.

219
00:13:45,824 --> 00:13:49,078
Someone saw him,

220
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,539
one of their miners.

221
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,667
Tonyo.

222
00:13:55,626 --> 00:13:57,294
There was a witness?

223
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:00,381
Why didn't you charge Amando Namas?

224
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:05,636
Because Tonyo died
before he could testify.

225
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:09,640
He died in the mine,

226
00:14:10,391 --> 00:14:13,060
buried in a collapsed tunnel.

227
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:19,567
I asked Namas after Tonyo died,

228
00:14:20,901 --> 00:14:22,736
but he denied everything.

229
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:26,991
After that,

230
00:14:27,616 --> 00:14:32,204
Sergeant Reynaldo stopped
all our investigations.

231
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:35,499
But,

232
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:38,377
I strongly believe

233
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:42,798
that everything Tonyo said

234
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:44,717
about Namas is true.

