00:15:33,223 --> 00:15:35,893
Sergeant Tupaz, I need help.

244
00:15:44,860 --> 00:15:47,321
Oh, my God. My son…

245
00:15:48,697 --> 00:15:52,910
Quiet, please. Please, baby.

246
00:15:52,993 --> 00:15:54,370
Aurora!

247
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:57,498
Give me back my son. You're evil.

248
00:15:57,581 --> 00:16:00,000
- Give me back my son.
- Aurora.

249
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:01,543
My son.

250
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,255
Mother.

251
00:16:12,096 --> 00:16:14,682
You fool. Give me back my son.

252
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:16,976
No.

253
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,771
- No.
- My son belongs to me.

254
00:16:20,854 --> 00:16:22,606
Paco's son belongs to me. No.

255
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:24,358
Give him back.

256
00:16:27,945 --> 00:16:28,904
Son…

257
00:16:34,451 --> 00:16:36,620
Mom, let's get out of here. Hold him.

258
00:16:36,704 --> 00:16:37,538
Give me the gun.

259
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:49,299
Sam, please be safe. Please.

260
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:51,260
<i>George?</i>

261
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:53,637
Sam…

262
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:57,182
Sam, what's going on? We heard gunshots.

263
00:16:57,850 --> 00:17:01,270
Have you found Aunt Mercy?
Aunt Aurora? Our baby?

264
00:17:01,770 --> 00:17:04,189
Yes, George. We got the baby
from Mom Aurora.

265
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:05,941
We're going there.

266
